1. Identify slide with vid
2. cmd + shift + c (to enter Inspect Elements)
3. click on video to find its code. 
    a. right-click on div --> Edit as HTML.
    b. if it's an empty div, the video is probably stored and hosted on a separate server. 
4. Within Inspect Elements, cmd + F to search keywords (e.g. 720p, 1080p)
5. Find the script that looks like the direct vid link.
6. Find and copy the direct link to the web browser.
7. Find download button and download. 